The paper deals with cross-modality person re-identification, which involves analyzing video data and learning common representations from different modalities. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for feature transfer, which involves learning discriminative and complementary shared and specific features of each modality. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with video analysis and modeling affinities, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
